["Flappy Bird","data:image/jpeg;base64,","<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Flappy Bird Game</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            margin: 0;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            background-color: #70c5ce;\n        }\n\n        canvas {\n            display: block;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            background-color: #70c5ce;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <canvas id=\"gameCanvas\"></canvas>\n\n    <script>\n        const canvas = document.getElementById(\"gameCanvas\");\n        const ctx = canvas.getContext(\"2d\");\n\n        canvas.width = 320;\n        canvas.height = 480;\n\n        const bird = {\n            x: 50,\n            y: canvas.height / 2,\n            width: 20,\n            height: 20,\n            speed: 0,\n            gravity: 0.6,\n            lift: -15,\n            draw() {\n                ctx.fillStyle = \"#FFFF00\";\n                ctx.fillRect(this.x, this.y, this.width, this.height);\n            },\n            update() {\n                this.speed += this.gravity;\n                this.y += this.speed;\n\n                if (this.y > canvas.height - this.height) {\n                    this.y = canvas.height - this.height;\n                    this.speed = 0;\n                }\n            },\n            jump() {\n                this.speed = this.lift;\n            }\n        };\n\n        const pipes = [];\n        const pipeWidth = 20;\n        const pipeGap = 100;\n        let frame = 0;\n        let gameOver = false;\n\n        function generatePipe() {\n            const height = Math.floor(Math.random() * (canvas.height - pipeGap));\n            pipes.push({ x: canvas.width, y: height });\n        }\n\n        function drawPipes() {\n            for (let i = 0; i < pipes.length; i++) {\n                ctx.fillStyle = \"#008000\";\n                ctx.fillRect(pipes[i].x, 0, pipeWidth, pipes[i].y);\n                ctx.fillRect(pipes[i].x, pipes[i].y + pipeGap, pipeWidth, canvas.height - pipes[i].y - pipeGap);\n                pipes[i].x -= 2;\n\n                if (pipes[i].x + pipeWidth < 0) {\n                    pipes.splice(i, 1);\n                    i--;\n                }\n\n                if (\n                    bird.x + bird.width > pipes[i].x &&\n                    bird.x < pipes[i].x + pipeWidth &&\n                    (bird.y < pipes[i].y || bird.y + bird.height > pipes[i].y + pipeGap)\n                ) {\n                    gameOver = true;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        function draw() {\n            ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n\n            bird.update();\n            bird.draw();\n\n            drawPipes();\n\n            if (frame % 60 === 0 && !gameOver) {\n                generatePipe();\n            }\n\n            if (gameOver) {\n                ctx.font = \"30px Arial\";\n                ctx.fillStyle = \"red\";\n                ctx.fillText(\"Game Over\", 100, canvas.height / 2);\n            }\n\n            frame++;\n            requestAnimationFrame(draw);\n        }\n\n        window.addEventListener(\"keydown\", (e) => {\n            if (e.key === \" \") {\n                bird.jump();\n            }\n        });\n\n        draw();\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"]
